text.section:
An employee organization may not:
interfere with, coerce, or restrain an employee in the exercise by the employee of any right under this subtitle;
cause or attempt to cause the Commission to discriminate against an employee in the exercise by the employee of any right under this subtitle;
coerce, discipline, fine, or attempt to coerce a member of an employee organization as punishment or reprisal;
coerce, discipline, fine, or attempt to coerce a member of an employee organization for the purpose of impeding the member's work performance;
refuse to negotiate in good faith with the Commission as required under § 18-207 of this subtitle; or
fail or refuse to cooperate in impasse procedures and impasse decisions as required under § 18-208 of this subtitle.
